                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13166.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-12T09:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1914, 9 a.m. No.
                                3</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s message for Zapata, September 7. The attempts to come to
                            some agreement with Zapata without the assistance of the United States,
                            though repeatedly suggested, have resulted in total failure and
                            increased friction. In fact actual fighting has occurred at several
                            places. The Department’s instructions concerning the President’s wishes
                            will not be overlooked and opportunity will be sought to bring the two
                            parties into agreement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
